premise_source_doc_sentence: Nationally , the 1912 election was the first United States presidential election since 1860 in which there were four candidates who each won more than five percent of the popular vote , the first since 1852 in which the ticket of a party other than the Democratic and Republican parties finished second , and the last altogether in which the ticket of a party other than the Democratic and Republican parties finished second .
